Uniq’s Pension Trustee Owners Looking to Sell Company, Sky Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-03-31T22:26:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/uniq-s-pension-trustee-owners-looking-to-sell-company-sky-says.html
Uniq Plc (UNIQ)  will be put up for sale
tomorrow by the pension trustees who own 90 percent of it, Sky
News City Editor Mark Kleinman  reported , without saying where he
got the information. The trustees hired Spayne Lindsay & Co LLP
to identify a buyer for the company, whose shares begin trading
on  London ’s AIM Market tomorrow, Kleinman said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 